From Ron Baalke Subject Re Keeping Spacecraft on after Funding Cuts In article A , James Thomas Green writes Why do spacecraft have to be shut off after funding cuts For example, Why couldn't Magellan just be told to go into a safe mode and stay bobbing about Venus in a low power use mode and if maybe in a few years if funding gets restored after the economy gets better hopefully , it could be turned on again It can be, but the problem is a political one, not a technical one Ron Baalke Jet Propulsion Lab M S Telos The aweto from New Zealand Pasadena, CA is part caterpillar and part vegetable